<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-10-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-10-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="536" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d536">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/695.]</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister to the
                                    Dominican Republic</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-25">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 25, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Commissioners think the <hi rend="italic">Wheeling, Prairie</hi> and
                            collier should be immediately supplemented with two more gunboats. No
                            more marines needed at present; none yet landed. Doyle expects to meet
                            Horacio Vásquez in a couple of days. New cabinet not yet announced.
                            Things moving slowly.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>